      "decision_type": "explore",
      "reward_rqm": 0.4801909148212894,
      "updated_q_value": 0.4776189425511032,
      "arm_count": 3,
      "time_seconds": 5.95287013053894,
      "hypothetical_doc": "**The Uncertainty Principle**, formulated by Werner Heisenberg, fundamentally states that there are inherent limits to our knowledge of certain pairs of physical properties simultaneously – specifically position and momentum.  Measuring one property with greater precision inevitably disturbs the other. This isn't a limitation of measurement technology; it’s an intrinsic aspect of quantum systems, leading to wave-particle duality and probabilistic behavior at the fundamental level.**"
